---
layout: layout-main.njk
title: "JamComments: Stupid-Simple, Static Comments"
---

{% macro transitionArrow (text, icon, id) %}
  <div class="bubble-slice">
    <span class="w-32 h-32">
      {% include icon %}
    </span>
    <a href="#{{id}}" class="text-2xl flex items-center font-thin pl-3" id="{{id}}">
      {{ text }}
    </span>
  </div>
{% endmacro %}

<div class="px-6">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-3">
    <div class="text-center pt-8 md:pt-12 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-bold text-4xl md:text-6xl leading-tight mb-4">Stupid-Simple Comments for the Jamstack</h1>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">
          statically rendered, ad-free, nothing fancy.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="block md:hidden text-center mt-12">
      {% include 'interest-button.njk' %}
    </div>

  <div class="mb-10 mt-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Your Jamstack blog isn't complicated. Comments shouldn't be either.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg">
          Today, options to collect &amp; display comments on your static site require either manually piecing together a hodge-podge of technologies, or selling yourself (and your readers) to a behemoth, soulless, third-party service. JamComments doesn't try to be anything other than a stupid-simple comment service that's easy to set up and doesn't leave you feeling guilty after doing so.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="my-12 md:my-16">
      {{ transitionArrow("The advantages are straightforward.", "svg/bulb.svg", "perks")  }}
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto">
      {% include 'home/highlights.njk' %}
    </div>

    <div class="my-12 md:my-16">
      {{ transitionArrow("And so is the pricing.", "svg/dollar.svg", "pricing")  }}
    </div>

  </div>

  {% include 'home/pricing.njk' %}

  <div class="my-12 md:my-16">
    {{ transitionArrow("So, choose your integration.", "svg/server.svg", "integrations")  }}
  </div>

  {% include 'home/integrations.njk' %}

  <hr class="max-w-3xl mx-auto block h-1 rounded-sm bg-gray-200 mt-5 mb-10 shadow-none border-0" />

  <div class="text-center mt-20">
    <span class="text-3xl font-thin mb-10 block">
      And that's the pitch. Now, sign up:
    </span>

    <a
      class="button button--inverse"
      href="{{ site.signUpUrl }}">
        Sign Up
    </a>
  </div>

</div>
